{"questionId":"9071430","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Urea, (H<sub>2</sub>N)<sub>2</sub>CO, is excreted by mammals and can be used as a fertilizer.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>The IR spectrum of urea is shown below.</p>\n<p><img src=\"https://ib-questionbank-attachments.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/tinymce_asset/asset/4570/Schermafbeelding_2018-08-09_om_14.21.30.png\" alt=\"M18/4/CHEMI/SP2/ENG/TZ1/01.h_01\"></p>\n<p>Identify the bonds causing the absorptions at 3450 cm<sup>−1</sup> and 1700 cm<sup>−1</sup> using section 26&nbsp;of the data booklet.</p>\n<p><img src=\"__IMG__/87dc7896a46cb8ac5dfdc91b86dbd8b635e99b20.png\"></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em>3450 cm</em><sup><em>–</em><em>1</em></sup><em>:</em>&nbsp;N–H</p>\n<p><em>1700 cm<sup>–1</sup>:</em>&nbsp;C=O</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Do </em><strong><em>not </em></strong><em>accept “O</em><em>–</em><em>H” for 3450 cm<sup>–1</sup></em><em>.</em></p>\n<p><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"9071430","referenceCode":"18M.2.sl.TZ1.h","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The IR spectrum of urea is shown below. Identify the bonds causing the absorptions at 3450 cm−1 and 1700 cm−1 using section 26 of the data booklet.","paper":"2","level":"SL","questionNumber":"h","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing","11.3 Spectroscopic identification of organic compounds","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}